children.content: Question: At what point do we alllocate to a Service Provider? Implicationsr: 1. Early allocation means DToS gives participant contact responsibility to SP 2. Late allocation means DToS has to provide participant contact capabilites
Key: Only required in a Service Provider Driven enviroment
Question: To what degree should the Programme care about Service Provider Capacity (ie rostering) Needs to consider: 1. Service Quality is impacted by non-availabiluity of capacity info
Question: Are we aiming to replace local/commercial Service Provider systems with nationally provided DToS Systems?
Question: Are we going ahead with Medium Risk Breast in St Georges as our first SEM/Integrated service?
Question: Is there general agreement that Screening ends with Diagnosis but will track follow up (provided by others) to allow E2E visibility?
Question: Do we all understand the concept of multiple SEMs? See analysis here https://nhsd-confluence.digital.nhs.uk/display/DTS/SEM+Variation+Analysis
Question: Do want to support multiple participant jouneys to test this out?

Question: Do we want participants to choose where they are screened and/or move between Service Providers. Implications: 1. Programme Capacity Mgmt is now uncertain. 2. May need to amend the Service Provide Commissioining Model to allow for intra-service provider participant movement?
Question: Do we want to run the adminstration of screening services centrally?
Question: Do we want to control the Customer Experience without involving the Service Provider?
Question: Who decides which appointment booking concept a Screenging Programme should use?

Question: If we do, is this for just the Admn part of the process or both the Admin and Screening Event? Implications: 1. Commissioning changes becuase Service Provider systems get restricted to just delivering SEMs? 2. DToS provision of Admin process.We have to replace all Comms and Admin to do this
In the future, Particpants will be allocated to a Slot at the most appropriate Service Provider rather that being allocated to a Service Provider during Service Planning

1. DToS will run screening administration services centrally. 2. DToS will facilitate a Shared Appointment Slot Calendar that will allow Service Poriders to manage slots locally and DToS to manage slots nationally. 2. Service Providers wil be commissined to provide SEM focused services 3. DToS will provide interfaces to Service Providers so that DToS servceos can be used through local systems (eg EPRs, GP Systems, LIMS etc) 4. DToS will allocate Particpants to Screening Slots and will faciltate the interactions with Participants 5. DToS will maintain a virtual Screening Call Centre. This will be used by one or more central teams providing mainline and overflow facilities. Local services can use the Call Center facilities to provide locally-focused responses.
Principles for this Model in its final state (Post Release 3)
